	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Aug 7th 11:35 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.39]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>1)Level 52 Enchanter. <br>2)I prefer a Druid Partner or a Druid/Shaman/Me Trio for most XP, but truly love gathering with friends in Deadly places. My favorite zones are L Guk (I have an office next to Dezlen the Paladin and Kager the Tank/Cleric. The King loves me!) Fungus Grove, Burning Woods, and Chardok<br>3)Solo is much more difficult anywhere but old world or Kunark (SoL HP's, damage and mob regen hurt), usually outdoors to give me room to see and stun/run/root. I prefer using a pet casting mez/dubuff/blur to open then poke and activate pet using Berserker Strength to 'heal' but will occasionally use charm 'kiting' if I have C3 on.<br>4)I truly love stretching my skills and pulling off 'the impossible'. I LOVE hearing about what you can't do then doing it. Went to FG 4th day and hunted Shadel Bandits with a 52Ranger MA, 51Druid and Shaman for Healers, a 46wizard, and 46 me. We killed 37 bandits 12 mushrooms and had only 1 death when the Uber Guild of our server trained us running for their lives. I've pulled out a LGuk train of 13 mobs, a Chardok Train of 9 at our exit camp, and had 7 Giants on Deck in BW. Controlled Chaos is meat and bread.<br>5)Group is indoor whenever I can, or chain duo pulls outdoors like ME, EJ, or Scarlet and the new JP<br>6) a-Group: 1 Root/AoE Mez(outdoors/indoors 2- Color Flux/Skew 3-Dazzle(never move) 4-Colorshift 5-Tash 6-ToT(casters near)or temporary buffs 7-Dot/DD/Debuff 8-Boon or Tricksters<br>b-solo 1Root 2Flux 3dazzle 4shift 5tash 6skew 7slow/DoT/DD 8berserk str Use DS from earring and swap spells during mez brakes<br>c-Duo is about the same but swap in Gflux, DD, DoT and Slow on the last 3 slots as situation demands and swap color flux for charm. LOVE that snare<br>7)main character though not my first. I have a 37Warrior, 36cleric, 31Rogue, 27Druid, 25BST, 25SK, 24Necro, 15ranger, 10bard. Started a shaman first then deleted him and then a rogue.<br>8)I love the control of a situation because you ARE all that stands between a bad pull and massive XP regardless what the MA or Cleric think. My job is to keep the whole party alive when they would have NO chance without me, and turn it into a Win situation.<br>&nbsp;<br>Aeldwan the Enchanter<br>Wanderers of the Realm<br>Morell-Thule<br>"Doing the improbable daily to make the impossible look easy"</td></tr>
